        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) to the pan with the <strong>drained tagliatelle</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and a generous splash of <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
